ing) so each client declares scan roots, per-language tool selection, size policy, and an enable flag. SCOPE IS SCHEMA-ONLY — this ticket does not change any metric runtime behavior and does not remove any hardcode; consuming the config + the Unavailable-on-unconfigured behavior land in migration 0734.\n\n## Review-driven corrections\n- Removed the \"replaces the hardcoded src/rebar / cap file\" and \"absent config -> code_health Unavailable\" claims: those hardcodes live in git_metrics.py and their removal + runtime fallback are 0734s job. This ticket only DEFINES the typed keys.\n- Name concrete keys/types in `_config_schema.py` dataclass.\n- Adding a section changes the pinned surface guard `tests/golden/config_surface.json` (checked by tests/unit/test_config_surface_golden.py) — regenerate + review it.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `[code_health]` dataclass in `_config_schema.py` with concrete keys: `enabled: bool=False`, `scan_roots: list[str]`, `analyzers: dict[str,str]` (lang->tool), `size_cap: int|None`, `size_near_fraction: float`.\n- [ ] Defaults documented; `rebar -c code_health.<key>=<val>` overrides parse via the existing path; section re-exported through config.py.\n- [ ] `tests/golden/config_surface.json` regenerated to include the section; golden test green.\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Unit: default load, `-c` override parse, missing-section default. Golden surface test passes.\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30 (interface). Recorded edge: depends_on 3b30.\n## Files likely touched: src/rebar/_config_schema.py, src/rebar/config.py, tests/golden/config_surface.json, tests/unit/test_code_health_config.py (new)\n## Estimated scope: M","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_config_schema.py","reason":"new [code_health] section dataclass: scan roots, per-language tool selection, size policy, enable flag"},{"path":"src/rebar/config.py","reason":"re-export new section accessors"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_code_health_config.